Subject: rPSA-2007-0243-1 flac

rPath Security Advisory: 2007-0243-1
Published: 2007-11-21
Products:
    rPath Linux 1

Rating: Minor
Exposure Level Classification:
    Indirect User Deterministic Unauthorized Access
Updated Versions:
    flac=conary.rpath.com@rpl:1/1.1.2-5.2-1

rPath Issue Tracking System:
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-1873

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2007-4619

Description:
    Previous versions of the flac package contain multiple integer overflow
    vulnerabilities that may result in heap-based buffer overflows, allowing
    an attacker to execute arbitrary code by providing malformed FLAC data
    to applications linked against libFLAC.

http://wiki.rpath.com/Advisories:rPSA-2007-0243

